Subject: Re: [T2] '71 intermittent problem

On Tue, Jul 01, 2003 at 01:37:30PM -0700, craig roche wrote:
> My '71 intermittently sputters and dies (as if it were running out
> of gas) while freeway driving. After a 5 or 10 minute roadside rest,
> I'm back on the road as if nothing happened. This will reoccur a day
> or week later. New points, plugs, condenser, coil and a cleaned
> float valve have not solved this problem.

So if it dies out usually only with a large fuel load I would suggest
changing the fuel filter, it's sure a cheap fix if it is infact the
problem. If that doesn't work, look into what pressure the fuel pump
is pumping, it might be going out & only doing part of it's job.


